    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI use `gq` to format comments, and it stopped working.\n\nThe reason is that `formatprg` is set to gofmt, so nvim tries to run \"gofmt\" which does nothing on comments.\n\nReason: \nThis line was recently introduced, that sets formatprg to `gofmt` for some reason. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blame/d3cded796c3b777148740726b7314783c9225946/runtime/ftplugin/go.vim#L19\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean test.go`\n3. Enter the following text:\n\n```go\npackage main\n\n// a very long comment that should be formatted when user presses `gq` on their keyboard.  This part should wrap to the next page with the comment prefix.\n```\n\n4. Position cursor on the line with comment\n5. Press `gql` to reformat (wrap) the line\n6. Nothing happens!\n7. Issue the following command: `:set formatprg=\"\"`\n8. Press `gql`\n9. The line is now reformatted.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect `gql` to reformat, or wrap comments\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.0 LuaJIT 2.1.1744318430\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, it doesn't\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacos 14.7.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nterminal.app, iterm2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbrew install neovim",
